 {"id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","content_hash":"08b7d826416ed0c2722457c544c53a66dbda28fa70f8f2cdae3a0b0bb9499437","title":"Operational status reporting","description":"Provide status responses in IPC (volumes, index stats, scheduler state), log periodic heartbeats, and surface UI indicators.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:30:17.820632364Z","updated_at":"2025-11-20T23:30:17.820632364Z","source_repo":".","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","depends_on_id":"ultrasearch-c00.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:34:24.221304571Z","created_by":"daemon"}],"comments":[{"id":4,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status 2025-11-20: IPC/status API requires IPC server and scheduler/index state structs; blocked until c00.2.x and c00.6.x land. When ready, will expose volumes/index stats/scheduler state and add heartbeat log.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:43:40Z"},{"id":11,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Config reference now lists status fields to expose: volumes (last_usn, journal_id, lag), indices (sizes/segments/last commit), scheduler state, metrics snapshot. Will align IPC Status response accordingly once IPC/service code exists.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:46:33Z"},{"id":25,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status API still pending IPC/scheduler state; blocked on workspace/editions and IPC schema convergence. Will implement once unblocked.","created_at":"2025-11-20T23:57:16Z"},{"id":30,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Extended IPC models for status: VolumeStatus now includes last_usn/journal_id; StatusResponse carries last_index_commit_ts and optional MetricsSnapshot (latencies, worker CPU/mem). Added optional timeout to SearchRequest for latency budgeting.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:00:37Z"},{"id":31,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Status IPC models extended (timeout in SearchRequest, last_usn/journal_id in VolumeStatus, last_index_commit_ts + MetricsSnapshot in StatusResponse). Server wiring still pending IPC/server design.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:00:56Z"},{"id":33,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Next steps: add server handling of StatusRequest (populate volume states, metrics snapshot, last_index_commit_ts) once IPC/server plumbing is ready.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:01:35Z"},{"id":37,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added service::status::make_status_response helper to populate new StatusResponse fields consistently; still needs real data wiring but models are now exercised via builder.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:42:33Z"},{"id":38,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Note: Duration serde in SearchRequest.timeout relies on std serde support (enabled by default); if workspace trims serde default features later, we must enable serde/std feature explicitly.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:42:50Z"},{"id":40,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Added unit tests covering SearchRequest timeout and VolumeStatus extended fields; more wiring pending once server-side available.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:44:00Z"},{"id":48,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"IPC tests added for timeout and volume fields; server wiring still pending and will proceed after manifest stabilizes.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:46:29Z"},{"id":51,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Aligned IPC schema with c00.6.1 updates: added metrics snapshot test, timeout/offset defaults in tests, fields queue_depth/active_workers retained. Service metrics snapshot now exposes queue_depth/active_workers placeholders.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:48:35Z"},{"id":53,"issue_id":"ultrasearch-c00.8.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Blocked on manifest/edition fixes before wiring StatusRequest handler; IPC schema aligned and tested.","created_at":"2025-11-21T00:49:18Z"}]}
